Below is a best-in-class breakdown of the components that should appear in a high-performing eCommerce welcome series—based on patterns from the top DTC brands (Athletic Greens, Chamberlain Coffee, Hims/Hers, Poppi, Liquid I.V., Hexclad, Caraway, Mud/Wtr, Olipop, and others), along with what consistently wins in Klaviyo performance data.

This is exactly what a world-class welcome series should include if the goal is maximum conversion, segmentation, education, and long-term retention.

⸻

Best-in-Class Components of a Welcome Series (Email by Email)

1. Welcome Email #1 — The “First Impression” (Sent Immediately)

Primary Objectives:
	•	Deliver the incentive (if any)
	•	Establish brand promise
	•	Get the first click ASAP
	•	Set expectations

Best-in-Class Components

1. A CTA Above the Fold
	•	“Shop Now,” “Claim Your Discount,” or “Take the Quiz”
	•	Needs to be visible instantly on mobile + desktop

2. Strong Hero With Clear Value Proposition
	•	What makes your brand different in 5 seconds
	•	Clean design + minimal text

3. A Single, Clear Offer or Action
	•	Do NOT include multiple conflicting CTAs
	•	Do not mention product categories—drive one action

4. Introduction to Brand Philosophy / Why You Exist
	•	1–2 lines max
	•	No brand autobiography

5. Immediate Social Proof
	•	“Trusted by 250,000 customers”
	•	Ratings, badges, UGC
	•	This boosts CTR dramatically

6. Quick-Scan USPs
Example:
	•	Clean ingredients
	•	30-day guarantee
	•	Free shipping over $X
	•	Doctor-backed

7. Visual Delivery of Discount or Benefit
	•	Coupon box graphic
	•	Button with the discount printed
	•	Reminder of the incentive

8. Footer With Key Navigation Links
	•	Shop
	•	Bestsellers
	•	Customer support

⸻

2. Welcome Email #2 — The “Why Us vs. Everyone Else” Email

Primary Objective:
Show the functional and emotional reasons your product is superior.

Best-in-Class Components

1. Comparison-Based Hero
	•	“Why 250,000 customers switched…”
	•	Contrast you vs competitors

2. Clear, Strong Benefit Explanation
	•	What pain do you remove?
	•	What transformation do you create?

3. USP Icons (3–5 max)
Examples:
	•	Clean ingredients
	•	Designed by experts
	•	Real clinical results
	•	Zero compromise

4. Social Proof Block
	•	UGC or short testimonials
	•	Preferably from customers who match quiz data (if applicable)

5. A Story With Stakes
	•	Brief founder story
	•	“We wanted a better way…”
	•	No long paragraphs

6. CTA Reinforcement
	•	“Try it today”
	•	“Find your perfect flavor”
	•	“Shop bestsellers”

⸻

3. Welcome Email #3 — The “Bestsellers + Discovery” Email

Primary Objective:
Help customers choose what to buy.

Best-in-Class Components

1. Hero Focused on Shopping, Not Storytelling
	•	“Meet Our Bestsellers”
	•	Above-the-fold CTA

2. Top-Selling Products With Reviews
	•	Each product block includes:
	•	Image
	•	Star rating
	•	One-line promise
	•	CTA “Shop Now”

3. Cross-Sell Discovery Pathways
	•	“Not sure where to start?”
	•	Collections such as:
	•	Best for beginners
	•	Most popular bundles
	•	Try-me sets

4. Delivery & Guarantee Block
	•	Returns
	•	Shipping speed
	•	Subscription flexibility

5. UGC or Lifestyle Anchor Image

⸻

4. Welcome Email #4 — The “Community + Social Proof” Email

Primary Objective:
Create emotional connection + long-term retention.

Best-in-Class Components

1. UGC-Driven Hero
	•	Real customer photo
	•	“You’re in good company”

2. Testimonial Wall
	•	3–5 curated reviews
	•	Each tied to tangible outcomes

3. Press Logos Strip
	•	“As seen in…”

4. Community Invitation
	•	Instagram
	•	TikTok
	•	Facebook group

5. Brand Values / Mission Snapshot
	•	Keep to bullet points
	•	Make it about the customer, not the founder

6. CTA → “See Why Customers Love Us”

⸻

5. Welcome Email #5 — The “Final Nudge” Email

Primary Objective:
Convert fence-sitters.

Best-in-Class Components

1. Hero With Urgency (Light, Not Hard Sell)
	•	“Your welcome offer expires soon”
	•	CTA above the fold

2. Objection Handling Section
Answer questions like:
	•	Will it work for me?
	•	What if I don’t like it?
	•	What flavors do people love?
	•	Is there a guarantee?

3. FAQ Block
	•	Shipping
	•	Returns
	•	Ingredients
	•	Subscription terms

4. Trust Anchors
	•	Certifications
	•	Awards
	•	Guarantee badges

5. Final CTA
	•	“Activate your code”
	•	“Complete your order”

⸻

Optional (But High Performing) Add-Ons

A. Pre-Welcome Email (When They Take Quiz or Join a List Without Incentive)
	•	“We got your answers”
	•	“Here’s what happens next”
	•	CTA → “View your recommendations”

B. Segmented Welcome Pathways

Based on:
	•	Quiz results
	•	Gender
	•	Product interest
	•	Problem type (e.g., bloating, low energy, dry skin)

C. New Subscriber 24-Hour VIP Offer Email
	•	Exclusive “first 24 hours only” deal
	•	Often converts better than standard offers

⸻

Best-in-Class Welcome Tech Stack Inside Klaviyo

1. Use Universal Blocks for Speed
	•	Header
	•	Footer
	•	Social icons
	•	USP block
	•	Review block
	•	Bestsellers grid
	•	Hero framework
	•	Offer section

2. Dynamic Personalization
	•	{{ first_name|default:‘friend’ }}
	•	{{ person.ViewedItems }}
	•	Quiz-based segmentation
	•	Conditional blocks based on preferences

3. Deliverability Best Practices
	•	CTA above the fold
	•	Lightweight images
	•	Keep HTML under 102KB
	•	Avoid large GIFs unless critical

⸻

The Formula for a Perfect Welcome Series

Every email should include:
	•	A clear CTA above the fold
	•	A single core message
	•	Social proof or validation
	•	Brand credibility
	•	Easy pathways to shop
	•	Minimal load time + compressed imagery

Across the entire series, you must include:
	•	Brand story
	•	Why we exist
	•	Why we’re better
	•	Why customers love us
	•	What to buy
	•	Removing buying friction
	•	Urgency + reminder

